title: For Sale:  Savage 99, .300 Savage, Dual Safeties
postcontent: I have for sale a Savage 99 chambered in .300 Savage.  It was made in 1946.  It's in beautiful condition.  What's unusual about it is that it has dual safeties--one on the tang and one on the lever, which are interconnected.  Savage made some transition models which had both safeties in 1960 when it transitioned from the lever safety to the tang safety.  However, this one is well before that.  There's not a lot of information out there on this gun as there's not that many out there with this configuration, but the best guess is that Savage may have offered a retrofit where the tang safety could be added to the earlier guns with the lever safety.  I also have a box and a half of shells to go with it.  I'm asking $500.  REDACTED

title: For Sale:  45mm Rainier Ballistics bullets for RELOADING
postcontent:
1 box of 500 45 cal 200gr RN $60

Rainier offers a large selection of swaged lead core copper plated bullets that are low in cost but substantially high in accuracy. Rainier swages their bullets twice with lead wire in an effort to ensure the tightest uniformity as well as prevention of premature wearing of barrels. While Rainier doesn't publish their own reloading information, they recommended using lead bullet load data when loading their bullets as well as a slight taper crimp. Rainier recommends a maximum velocity of 1,500 fps. 

These bullets feature a lead core that is completely covered by copper plating. They are resized after being plated with approximately 0.004" of copper plating. This unique design makes them suitable for most indoor ranges, which often require the use of bullets with no exposed lead. The base is slightly concave to maximize the bullet to bore seal.

title: For Sale:  Leupold Mark 4 LR/T Illuminated TMR 4.5-14x50mm
postcontent:
Hi Im selling my Leupold Mark 4 illuminated TMR reticle 4.5-14x50mm (30mm main tube). I had this scope for a little over a month (still have box). Reason Im selling is that I was planning on doing more long range shooting than I actually have time for (or the money). This scope was going to be used as duel use for long range shooting and (long range) hunting. The fact that it is illuminated helps with the first and last minutes of hunting when it is still dark outside. Each level of illumination has an off between each level of brightness (which is much better than Nightforce scopes that have a preset level of brightness which cant be changed quickly). The glass on this scope is as clear as you will ever see. This is almost the best scope that I have owned, but when you get into such high-end quality scopes, the difference in quality is hard to tell. I need the money right now for another project and because I am not using this scope to its fullest potential. 

The scope is in like brand new condition. It is currently held by Burris extreme tactical rings (low), that have been lapped. Lapping reduces any pressure points the rings can put on the scope from any manufacture imperfections on the rings. This translates into a better secured scope and equal pressure all around the body of the scope. 

The anti-cant is a Holland Signature Series. I believe this is the best anti cant as it is very clear and strong yet not bulky. 

The rail is an EGW 20 MOA rail for a Remington 700 Long Action. A small part of the rail was cut off (by a gun smith) on the front end so the scope would not be so close to the end of the rail.

Scope $1400

Originally marketed for airsoft use but don't let that dissuade you, these are rugged enough for real steel.  They have torture tested another pair for over 50,000 rounds and they still hold zero just as well as the first day we installed them.


Note: This laser grip fits 99.9% of manufactured full sized 1911 pistols, however due to the great number of different 1911 manufacturers and dimensional differences between them, there are a small number of pistols these grips may not fit. For example, very slim frames may require a shim between the frame and pressure switch to properly activate it, while very fat frames may create a point of aim for the laser that is outside of the range of the windage and elevation adjustment screws to correct for.
Very similar to Crimson Trace grips.

title: For Sale:  Finnish M27 Mosin Nagant 1939 Tikka Antique!
postcontent:
Here's a real pretty Finish M27 Mosin Nagant long rifle.
It's a 1939 Tikka and was built around an 1897 Tula receiver.
This officially qualifies it as an "Antique".
Numbers match - but it is the typical "Finn Matching" meaning that they built the rifle out of a mixture of Finn made and Russian made parts - then match-numbered them.

Stock is a nice pre-war round splice stock.  The butt appears to be Walnut and has some beautiful tiger striping.

The M27 is a heavy barrel version of the original 1891 Mosin Nagant Infantry rifle.  These rifles are known for their accuracy and top notch fitting by the Finn armorers.

Finnish leather Sling is included

Caliber is 7.62x54R.  

Rifling is crisp and sharp.

Please email if you have any questions or want to see some more pictures.

This rifle classifies as an Antique because of the 1897 Receiver date.  As such - no FFL is required for purchase or shipment to another state.  Please see receiver tang pic.

I would prefer to sell this rifle face to face, but I will consider shipping.  Please email me if you inquire about shipping.
